  "prompt": "Can a msc chemistry student apply for ISRO summer internship?",
  "response": "Yes, an M.Sc. Chemistry student can apply for the ISRO (Indian Space Research Organisation) summer internship, subject to certain conditions:\n\n1. Eligibility Criteria:\n- The student should be currently pursuing M.Sc. in Chemistry\n- Usually, students in the final year or pre-final year are preferred\n- Age limit typically ranges between 18-35 years\n\n2. Application Process:\n- Check ISRO's official website regularly for internship announcements\n- Look for specific internship programs in chemistry-related domains\n- Follow the application guidelines mentioned in the notification\n\n3. Potential Areas of Work:\n- Material sciences\n- Chemical research\n- Analytical chemistry\n- Space material development\n\n4. Important Recommendations:\n- Maintain good academic performance\n- Have relevant research experience or projects\n- Prepare a strong resume\n- Be ready for potential technical interviews\n\n5. Additional Tips:\n- Apply well before the deadline\n- Read the instructions carefully\n- Highlight your relevant skills and achievements\n\nNote: Specific eligibility and selection criteria may vary each year, so always refer to the latest official notification from ISRO for the most accurate and current information.",
